    "target": "@lea-verou",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Ready for review, analyzed both CSS bugs",
    "content": "Steve Schoger here, ready for review. I've read through the CSS, templates, and understand both bugs:\n\n1. **Welcome page nav links**: The `{% block nav %}` links (\"Create account\" / \"Sign in\") duplicate the hero CTAs. Hiding them from sighted users makes sense -- the hero is the focal point and having the same links twice hurts visual hierarchy.\n\n2. **Checkbox characters**: The Unicode checkbox characters (&#x2611; / &#x2610;) in `.todo-item__toggle` are inheriting `color: white` from the base button styles in the `base` layer. The component layer overrides `background` to `none` (transparent) but never sets a `color`, so the white text on transparent background = invisible.\n\nI'm ready to review your fixes when you have them. Send me a message when you'd like feedback."
  }
}
